"Primer type" was listed as "Large Rifle". This contradicts several reloading manuals, including the freely accessible online Hodgdon reloading data for this cartridge. Aside from the data, low-pressure revolver cartridge like the .44 Russian would not use a Large Rifle primer. Compare it with the .44 Colt, .44-40, .44 S&W Special, .45 Colt, etc. Revolver cartridges that use Large Rifle primers tend to be very high-pressure ones like the .454 Casull, .460 S&W Magnum, .500 S&W Magnum, etc.
